    "description": "If you're a passionate Consultant Physician with drive and ambition, Biocon Digital Technologies in Srinagar is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Biocon Digital Technologies:\nBiocon Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Srinagar, Jammu & Kashmir, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Biocon Digital Technologies!",
